To generate all permutations of a list, consider using a recursive approach that selects each element in turn and generates all permutations of the remaining elements. 
```python
def all_permutations(xs):
    if len(xs) == 1:
        return [tuple(xs)]
    result = []
    for i, x in enumerate(xs):
        rest = xs[:i] + xs[i+1:]
        for p in all_permutations(rest):
            result.append((x,) + p)
    return sorted(result)
```
